1
00:00:17,951 --> 00:00:21,871
<Now the latest weather forecast
<for northwest Koriko.

2
00:00:22,523 --> 00:00:25,273
<Skies are clearing up,
<thanks to a high-pressure front...

3
00:00:25,759 --> 00:00:28,419
<moving in from the continent.

4
00:00:28,896 --> 00:00:31,856
<Mild winds will be
<blowing in from the west...

5
00:00:32,366 --> 00:00:34,916
<clearing out the clouds
<by this evening.

6
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:37,919
<We'll also have
<a beautiful full moon tonight...

7
00:00:38,372 --> 00:00:41,802
<so pack up your picnic baskets because
<the weather is going to be just fine.

8
00:00:44,144 --> 00:00:46,833
<More news in just a minute.

9
00:00:48,081 --> 00:00:50,631
<First this word from
<the courteous people at Central Market.

10
00:01:20,013 --> 00:01:23,233
Jiji, I've decided!
I'm gonna do it tonight!

11
00:01:23,784 --> 00:01:26,244
Mom! Hey! I decided!

12
00:01:26,687 --> 00:01:29,407
Oh, hi, Miss Dora.
It's gonna be completely clear tonight.

13
00:01:29,890 --> 00:01:33,080
I heard the weather forecast.
There's gonna be a big full moon.

14
00:01:33,627 --> 00:01:36,377
Did you borrow your father's radio
without permission again?

15
00:01:36,863 --> 00:01:38,383
Is it okay? I'm sorry!

16
00:01:39,366 --> 00:01:41,036
Happy to see you, Miss Dora.

17
00:01:41,368 --> 00:01:43,327
Mom, my mind's made up.
It's tonight.

18
00:01:43,704 --> 00:01:45,874
Weren't you gonna
put it off a month?

19
00:01:46,273 --> 00:01:48,463
But the next full moon
might be on a cloudy night.

20
00:01:48,875 --> 00:01:51,715
I want to make sure I leave
on the perfect night.

21
00:01:52,212 --> 00:01:53,882
Kiki, wait!

22
00:01:57,384 --> 00:02:00,224
My, my.
What's this leaving business?

23
00:02:00,721 --> 00:02:02,651
It's one of our old customs.

24
00:02:03,023 --> 00:02:06,243
When a witch turns 13 she leaves home
for a year to begin her training.

25
00:02:07,527 --> 00:02:09,747
Your little baby is 13?

26
00:02:10,163 --> 00:02:12,683
My, my. Time flies so quickly,
doesn't it?

27
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:15,823
I'm afraid so. But nobody
leaves home that young anymore.

28
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:18,670
l remember perfectly well...

29
00:02:19,006 --> 00:02:21,816
the exact day
you arrived in this town.

30
00:02:22,309 --> 00:02:24,448
A little 13-year-old girl
came down from the sky...

31
00:02:24,845 --> 00:02:27,475
riding a broomstick,
her eyes shining.

32
00:02:27,948 --> 00:02:31,608
I thought you were
a bit stuck-up.

33
00:02:32,219 --> 00:02:34,329
But Kiki doesn't know much
besides flying.

34
00:02:34,721 --> 00:02:36,391
She hardly knows any
of my formulas.

35
00:02:37,290 --> 00:02:39,920
After I'm gone,
who will make this medicine?

36
00:02:40,394 --> 00:02:42,004
Sign of the times,
I'm afraid.

37
00:02:42,329 --> 00:02:44,079
Everything changes,
bit by bit.

38
00:02:44,431 --> 00:02:48,471
But I have to say,
nothing works as well for my rheumatism.

39
00:02:50,437 --> 00:02:53,897
You're always telling me to hurry!
Now who's the slowpoke?

40
00:02:54,474 --> 00:02:59,013
I think it's better to leave
with decorum and great dignity.

41
00:02:59,746 --> 00:03:03,726
If we put it off for a month, and I find
some wonderful boyfriend, then what?

42
00:03:04,384 --> 00:03:06,164
We'll never leave!

43
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:09,130
I'm worried about this.
Once you've decided, you can't go back.

44
00:03:09,589 --> 00:03:11,519
Of course.
I know that.

45
00:03:11,892 --> 00:03:12,972
Good. It's there.

46
00:03:13,226 --> 00:03:16,216
I'm so excited!
It's like getting a birthday present!

47
00:03:21,568 --> 00:03:22,678
You won't believe it, Dad!

48
00:03:22,936 --> 00:03:25,156
I've decided
to go away tonight!

49
00:03:25,572 --> 00:03:28,002
- Tonight?
- Yeah! I just decided!

50
00:03:28,442 --> 00:03:31,872
Well, yes, but what about
our camping trip for this weekend?

51
00:03:32,446 --> 00:03:33,816
Sorry, Dad!

52
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:47,448
Yes. I'll expect you then.
Thanks.

53
00:03:51,431 --> 00:03:54,591
Hi, Mom. I wanted to make sure
you knew that Kiki is leaving tonight.

54
00:03:55,135 --> 00:03:56,215
Yes, at midnight.

55
00:04:01,675 --> 00:04:04,805
- Not bad.
- wish it were a different color.

56
00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:08,065
Witches have worn this color
for over a thousand years.

57
00:04:09,349 --> 00:04:11,629
Black cat, black clothes.

58
00:04:12,052 --> 00:04:14,452
It's not really important
what color your dress is.

59
00:04:14,888 --> 00:04:17,138
What matters is
the heart inside it.

60
00:04:17,557 --> 00:04:20,107
I know that having a good heart
is very important.

61
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:23,110
I wish I could show you
that my heart is ready.

62
00:04:23,563 --> 00:04:25,233
Just follow that heart
and keep smiling.

63
00:04:25,565 --> 00:04:27,525
Okay.

64
00:04:27,901 --> 00:04:31,001
Be sure to write home
as soon as you've found a place.

65
00:04:32,572 --> 00:04:34,622
Dad, can I please
take the radio?

66
00:04:35,008 --> 00:04:37,378
Mom, you said
I could have his radio.

67
00:04:37,811 --> 00:04:40,390
<- Yea!
<- Well, the radio's yours now.

68
00:04:40,847 --> 00:04:43,837
Okay. Now let me have
a look at my little witch.

69
00:04:52,058 --> 00:04:53,868
You look just like your mother did
when she was your age.

70
00:04:54,227 --> 00:04:56,037
Dad...

71
00:04:56,396 --> 00:04:58,586
would you pick me up
like you used to?

72
00:04:58,999 --> 00:05:00,289
Well...

73
00:05:12,512 --> 00:05:15,912
How come you never told me
you were growing up so fast?

74
00:05:16,483 --> 00:05:19,033
You can always come home
if things don't work out.

75
00:05:19,486 --> 00:05:21,736
Come back to my old room?
No, thanks.

76
00:05:25,358 --> 00:05:27,028
I hope you find a good town.

77
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:41,645
I bet it's real tough to find
a town to live in by yourself.

78
00:05:42,142 --> 00:05:43,952
Don't worry.
Kiki will be fine.

79
00:05:44,311 --> 00:05:47,001
- What kind of town are you looking for?
- A big town?

80
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:49,700
Yeah.
By the ocean, I hope.

81
00:05:50,116 --> 00:05:52,666
-Wow!
- I'm so jealous of you!

82
00:05:53,119 --> 00:05:57,719
But I'm not going for a good time.
I'll be in training at least a year.

83
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:01,068
Yeah, but they'll have discos,
won't they?

84
00:06:04,097 --> 00:06:06,496
- Kiki, it's almost time.
- Okay!

85
00:06:08,668 --> 00:06:10,338
That's the broom
you're leaving on?

86
00:06:10,670 --> 00:06:13,160
Yeah. I just made it.
Pretty cute, huh?

87
00:06:13,607 --> 00:06:17,297
It's cute, but you can't start witching
on a broom that's too small. Take mine.

88
00:06:17,911 --> 00:06:19,581
But, Mom, that one's so old.

89
00:06:19,913 --> 00:06:24,483
That's why you should have it.
It never loses its way, even in a storm.

90
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:27,268
Kiki, trust me.

91
00:06:27,654 --> 00:06:30,494
But I worked so hard on it.
Right, Jiji?

92
00:06:30,991 --> 00:06:33,390
Your mother's broom would be better.

93
00:06:33,827 --> 00:06:35,317
You rotten traitor.

94
00:06:35,629 --> 00:06:40,379
He's right. You can make yourself
another broom when you get settled down.

95
00:06:47,474 --> 00:06:49,664
- Be careful.
- Go get ‘em.

96
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,630
- Bye!
- Have a good time!

97
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:03,712
Go, go, Kiki!
Go, go, Kiki!

98
00:07:15,902 --> 00:07:18,452
She hasn't got the hang of it yet.

99
00:07:25,979 --> 00:07:28,669
She's well past the lake
and doing just fine.

100
00:07:29,149 --> 00:07:32,139
I'm going to miss the sound
of that little bell.

101
00:07:39,526 --> 00:07:40,896
Which way are we headed?

102
00:07:41,194 --> 00:07:43,034
I think south, to the ocean.

103
00:07:48,335 --> 00:07:52,174
Climb up and turn on the radio.
I don't think I can.

